Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired filtration. The presence of glucose and ketones in urine, despite normal blood glucose and low HbA1c, may indicate tubular dysfunction rather than diabetes. Urine abnormalities (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) further support renal pathology. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
